text.p: Placements of broiler chicks in the 15 major producing states in the week ended Sept 7 totalled 132.615 million, versus a revised 133.822 million in the previous week and 130.447 million a year ago, the U.S. Agriculture Department said.
Eggs set in those states in the same week totalled 164.010 million, versus a revised 164.549 million the previous week and 157.422 million in the comparable week of last year, USDA said.
